=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from 3-chloro-4,5-bis(hydroxymethyl)pyridine. | Step 2: Monoprotect one primary alcohol as the TBDMS ether to give 4-OTBS-3-chloro-5-(hydroxymethyl)pyridine (regioisomer chosen so the free CH2OH is the future amine site). | Step 3: Convert the free primary alcohol to the bromide (PBr3 or Appel), then displace with NaN3 to form 4-OTBS-3-chloro-5-(azidomethyl)pyridine. | Step 4: Reduce the azide to the aminomethyl group and deprotect TBDMS to furnish 5-(aminomethyl)-4-hydroxymethyl-3-chloropyridine. | Step 5: Acylate the amine with isobutyryl chloride (base, e.g. DIPEA) to reach CC(C)C(=O)NCc1cncc(Cl)c1CO.

